main event: Radar tracking of unidentified flying objects over the Atlantic Ocean near the Azores Islands on July 3, 1954.
interesting points: The radar operator, Captain Spain, observed an unusual radar return that he could not identify.
The objects appeared as a symmetrical group of 7 circular objects on the radar scope.
The objects moved at high speeds, were tracked for 14 minutes, and then disappeared off the radar.
The radar operator reset the antenna tilt and camera to further investigate the unidentified radar returns.
A later investigation by radar and photo interpreters could not conclusively identify the nature of the radar returns.
sighted object: symmetrical group of 7 circular objects on radar
location: Atlantic Ocean near the Azores Islands
